    "created_at": "2023-04-08T17:59:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-04-08T17:59:01Z",
    "body": "For anyone that's installed starship/nu with Nix using `home-manager`, using the provided `programs.nushell.envFile.text` option to configure the `env.nu` file results in the `starship init nu | save ...` line being appended onto the end of the file, if `programs.starship.enableNushellIntegration` is set to true. The current workaround I'm using for this is to explicitly set the contents of the `env.nu` with the above solution by doing:\r\n```nix\r\nxdg.configFile.\"nushell/env.nu\".text = ''\r\n  # ...\r\n  starship init nu\r\n  | str replace --string 'PROMPT_COMMAND = {' 'PROMPT_COMMAND = { ||'\r\n  | str replace --string 'PROMPT_COMMAND_RIGHT = {' 'PROMPT_COMMAND_RIGHT = { ||'\r\n  | save -f ~/.cache/starship/init.nu\r\n''\r\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "pin": null,
